            def self.language_project_trend_current(start_date = nil, end_date =  nil)

            def self.update_project_files repo, token, try_n = 3
        
      126. 
      
        
    126. 
          
          
              project_files = nil
        
      127. 
      
        
    127. 
          
          
              repo = repo.deep_symbolize_keys if repo.respond_to? "deep_symbolize_keys"

    128.

    129.

      131.

    137.

      140. 
      
        
    140.

            def self.update_branches repo, token
        
      153. 
      
        
    153.

    163.

      164.

      165. 
      
        
    165. 
          
          
                repo[:branches] = branches
        
      166.

      168.

    169. 
          
          
              repo
        
      170. 
      
        
    170.

          2

      180.

          2

          2

            def self.create_or_update_repos user, data

            def self.paging_for response, page = 1, per_page = 30
        
      200. 
      
        
    200. 
          5
          
              paging = {
        
      201.

            def self.fetch_project_file_from_branch repo_name, filename, branch = "master", token = nil
        
      243. 
      
        
    243. 
          13
          
              branch_info = Github.repo_branch_info repo_name, branch, token
        
      244. 
      
        
    244. 
          13
          
              if branch_info.nil? || branch_info[:commit].nil?
        
      245. 
      
        
    245. 
          3
          
                log.error "fetch_project_file_from_branch - can't read branch info for [repo_name: #{repo_name}, branch: #{branch}, token: #{token}] - branch_info: #{branch_info}"
        
      246. 
      
        
    246. 
          3
          
                return nil
        
      247. 
      
        
    247. 
          
          
              end
        
      248. 
      
        
    248. 
          
          
          
        
      249. 
      
        
    249. 
          10
          
              file_info = Github.project_file_info( repo_name, filename, branch_info[:commit][:sha], token)
        
      250. 
      
        
    250. 
          10
          
              if file_info.nil? || file_info.empty?
        
      251. 
      
        
    251. 
          
          
                log.error %Q{
        
      252. 
      
        
    252. 
          
          
                  fetch_project_file_from_branch | can't read info about project's file.
        
      253. 
      
        
    253. 
          
          
                  repo: #{repo_name} , filename: `#{filename}` , branch_info: #{branch_info}
        
      254. 
      
        
    254. 
          
          
                }
        
      255. 
      
        
    255. 
          
          
                return nil
        
      256. 
      
        
    256. 
          
          
              end
        
      257. 
      
        
    257. 
          
          
          
        
      258. 
      
        
    258. 
          10
          
              file_content = fetch_file(file_info[:url], token)
        
      259. 
      
        
    259. 
          10
          
              return nil if file_content.nil?
        
      260. 
      
        
    260. 
          
          
          
        
      261. 
      
        
    261. 
          10
          
              file_info.merge({
        
      262. 
      
        
    262. 
          
          
                branch: branch,
        
      263. 
      
        
    263. 
          
          
                content: file_content[:content]
        
      264. 
      
        
    264. 
          
          
              })
        
      265.

            end

            def self.project_file_info(git_project, filename, sha, token)
        
      270. 
      
        
    270. 
          10
          
              url   = "#{Settings.instance.github_api_url}/repos/#{git_project}/git/trees/#{sha}?recursive=1"
        
      271. 
      
        
    271. 
          10
          
              tree = get_json(url, token)
        
      272. 
      
        
    272.
